    &lt;CommentText&gt;I had an appointment last week at outpatients B.  
During the examination the Dr. used an eye glass to look at the back of my eyes.  
Since the appointment I have had a terrible reaction on both my eyes so much so that I can't wear my contact lenses and I have gone to a pharmacist who has prescribed some hydro cortisone cream.  
I don't think it was the drops you administered but I think it is from the eye glass that was used.  
At no point did the Dr. wipe the glass before or after using it on my eyes/face.  
I don't have any allergies however, I don't know what the previous person uses on their face.  
I do think this eye glass should be cleaned before each new patient.  
As there are hand cleansers all over the hospital hygiene is one of your priorities..&lt;/CommentText&gt;
